This paper deals with the profitability of deviant mining strategies in Bitcoin's network protocol, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses martingale techniques, which are commonly used in the study of probability and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves game theory and optimization, which are relevant to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the study of revenue ratios, which is relevant to the category of network economics (cs.NE).
